# Copy to `.dev.vars` — secrets the Worker reads in local dev (miniflare).
# Non-secret config (NEON_AUTH_URL, ADMIN_EMAILS, LIBBY_LIBRARY_KEY) lives in
# wrangler.jsonc `vars`, not here.

# Neon pooled connection string (same value as DATABASE_URL in .env).
DATABASE_URL="postgresql://user:password@ep-xxxx-pooler.region.aws.neon.tech/dbname?sslmode=require"

# --- Optional integrations ---------------------------------------------------

# Movie/TV scrape-assist. Books (Open Library) and movies/TV (Wikidata, CC0)
# work with NO key. TMDB is richer but its free tier is non-commercial only.
# TMDB_API_KEY=""

# Billing (Stripe). Leave unset to keep billing dormant (endpoints return 501).
# Create a recurring $1.99/mo price in Stripe, then fill all three:
# STRIPE_SECRET_KEY="sk_test_..."
# STRIPE_PRICE_STANDARD="price_..."          # the Standard plan price id
# STRIPE_WEBHOOK_SECRET="whsec_..."          # from `stripe listen` (dev) or the dashboard
